{"unit": "fab-the-red-dragon-and-the-gold-17-p03", "kind": "event", "name": "Citadel sends white ravens", "quote": "the Citadel of Oldtown sent forth three hundred white ravens", "line": 149, "hedge_term": "mushroom", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-red-dragon-and-the-gold-17-p03", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Rhaenyra Targaryen", "slug": "rhaenyra-targaryen", "text": "Every time she sat the Iron Throne, its blades drew fresh blood from her", "line": 57, "hedge_term": "eustace", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-red-dragon-and-the-gold-17-p03", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Mysaria", "slug": "mysaria", "text": "The White Worm, a Lysene harlot who came from the shadows to reside in the Red Keep, known as Lady Misery, mistress of whisperers in all but name", "line": 55, "hedge_term": "eustace", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-red-dragon-and-the-gold-17-p03", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Mysaria", "slug": "mysaria", "text": "Prince Daemon remained in her thrall", "line": 55, "hedge_term": "eustace", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-red-dragon-and-the-gold-17-p03", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Maelor Targaryen", "slug": "maelor-targaryen", "text": "A washerwoman, Willow Pound-Stone, tore him from the dying knight's arms", "line": 77, "hedge_term": "mushroom", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-red-dragon-and-the-gold-17-p03", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Maelor Targaryen", "slug": "maelor-targaryen", "text": "His head was sent to King's Landing with the knight's corpse", "line": 83, "hedge_term": "mushroom", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-red-dragon-and-the-gold-17-p03", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Willow Pound-Stone", "slug": "willow-pound-stone", "text": "A washerwoman who took Maelor from the dying knight, calling him her new son", "line": 77, "hedge_term": "mushroom", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-red-dragon-and-the-gold-17-p03", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Lady Caswell", "slug": "lady-caswell", "text": "She hanged those responsible for Maelor's death and sent the knight's corpse and the prince's head to King's Landing", "line": 83, "hedge_term": "mushroom", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-red-dragon-and-the-gold-17-p03", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Garibald Grey", "slug": "garibald-grey", "text": "He commanded the queen's men and called the rout \"butchery, not battle\"", "line": 143, "hedge_term": "mushroom", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-red-dragon-and-the-gold-17-p03", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Byron Swann", "slug": "byron-swann", "text": "The accounts dispute which dragon; all agree the ruse brought only his death", "line": 147, "hedge_term": "mushroom", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-red-dragon-and-the-gold-17-p03", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Byron Swann", "slug": "byron-swann", "text": "The dragon melted his mirrored shield and roasted him", "line": 149, "hedge_term": "mushroom", "hedge_distance": 0}
